  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hands-On Learning for Zambia&apos;s Orphans and their communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There are large numbers of orphans and vulnerable children in Zambia, due to poverty, and HIV. These children, especially the girls, are less likely to go to school, and almost half of them fail to get through primary school. This project works closely with communities to work out what the hardest challenges are for local children, and how they can overcome them. It will also work with the government to make sure they are targeting the problems the communities have identified. The project will support these vulnerable children&#x2019;s schooling and help Zambia come up with an effective plan for the future.</narrative>
  </description>
